  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "This RFC is regarding distributing typedef files with React. While this would be generally useful (and possibly useful to extract the [React.js definitions](https://github.com/facebook/flow/blob/master/lib/react.js) out of flow itself (especially for renderer-implementers), it would be especially nice for renderer implementers.\r\n\r\n(I have manually extracted the minimal required for a react renderer in https://github.com/iamdustan/tiny-react-renderer/tree/fiber/src/fiber-types)\r\n\r\nPossible solutions:\r\n\r\n* ensure `flow gen-flow-files ....` works and generates all of the `*.js.flow` files in packages\r\n* add a custom step to the build tooling to include the public renderer type def for each public package + a minimal typedef for `ReactFiberReconciler.js` in each package that receives that file.",
